owl:Ontology.rdfs:comment: Describes entities and relationships belonging to objects in an institutional repository, with special attention to the needs of the Education and Research Archive at the University of Alberta. Utilizes external authorities and ontologies wherever possible.
owl:Ontology.rdfs:label: Jupiter Ontology

owl:AnnotationProperty.terms:description: Typically, the subject will be represented using keywords, key phrases, or classification codes. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Subject
owl:AnnotationProperty.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

owl:ObjectProperty.obo:IAO_0000112: The source of the public description and this info is found here: http://bibotools.googlecode.com/svn/bibo-ontology/trunk/doc/index.html. Bibo considers this term "unstable". The bibo editorial note is: "We are not defining, using an enumeration, the range of the bibo:degree to the defined list of bibo:ThesisDegree. We won't do it because we want people to be able to define new degress if needed by some special usecases. Creating such an enumeration would restrict this to happen."
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: degree
related degree
owl:ObjectProperty.skos:editorialNote: We are not defining, using an enumeration, the range of the bibo:degree to the defined list of bibo:ThesisDegree. We won't do it because we want people to be able to define new degress if needed by some special usecases. Creating such an enumeration would restrict this to happen.
owl:ObjectProperty.skos3:editorialNote: We are not defining, using an enumeration, the range of the bibo:degree to the defined list of bibo:ThesisDegree. We won't do it because we want people to be able to define new degress if needed by some special usecases. Creating such an enumeration would restrict this to happen.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The publication status of (typically academic) content.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: status
owl:ObjectProperty.skos:editorialNote: We are not defining, using an enumeration, the range of the bibo:status to the defined list of bibo:DocumentStatus. We won't do it because we want people to be able to define new status if needed by some special usecases. Creating such an enumeration would restrict this to happen.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The University where the graduating student was enrolled.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Institution

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The Digital Object Identifier, DOI, for the article.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Digital Object Identifier

owl:DatatypeProperty.terms:description: Examples of a Contributor include a person, an organization, or a service. Typically, the name of a Contributor should be used to indicate the entity.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: An entity responsible for making contributions to the resource.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Contributor

owl:DatatypeProperty.terms:description: Examples of a Creator include a person, an organization, or a service. Typically, the name of a Creator should be used to indicate the entity.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: An entity primarily responsible for making the resource.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Creator

owl:DatatypeProperty.terms:description: Typically, rights information includes a statement about various property rights associated with the resource, including intellectual property rights.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Information about rights held in and over the resource.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Rights

owl:DatatypeProperty.terms:description: Typically, the subject will be represented using keywords, key phrases, or classification codes. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Subject

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Date on which the resource was changed.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Date Modified

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A name given to the resource.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Title

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A person responsible for making the thesis.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Dissertant

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A person who was a member of a group of persons responsible for evaluating and approving the student's thesis.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Commitee Member

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A distinct, usually specialized educational unit within an educational organization responsible for the degree program to which the graduating student belonged.
Example: "Department of Biological Sciences" or "Department of Chemistry"
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Department

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: User responsible for depositing the resource
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Depositor

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Date student graduated from degree program.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Graduation Date

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Person responsible for the role of advising the graduating student.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Supervisor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: a set of requests/permissions to users of a Work, e.g. a copyright license, the public domain, information for distributors
owl:Class.rdfs:label: License

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An AlternateOrder is an alternate ordering of its parent's members. It should only order the parent's members, and otherwise has all of the features of ordering (some members may be omitted from the order, members may appear more than once in the order, etc.).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Alternate Order

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Collection is a group of resources. Collections have descriptive metadata, access metadata, and may links to works and/or collections. By default, member works and collections are an unordered set, but can be ordered using the ORE Proxy class.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Collection

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A File is a sequence of binary data and is described by some accompanying metadata. The metadata typically includes at least basic technical metadata (size, content type, modification date, etc.), but can also include properties related to preservation, digitization process, provenance, etc. Files MUST be contained by exactly one Object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: File

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An Object is an intellectual entity, sometimes called a "work", "digital object", etc. Objects have descriptive metadata, access metadata, may contain files and other Objects as member "components". Each level of a work is therefore represented by an Object instance, and is capable of standing on its own, being linked to from Collections and other Objects. Member Objects can be ordered using the ORE Proxy class.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Object

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A group of related Files, typically a single master File and its derivatives.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: FileSet

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A section of a Work, corresponding to a IIIF Range. Has member FileSets representing the physical parts of the Work are part of the section (e.g., which pages are in a chapter).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Range

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A logical ordering of the component parts of a Work, corresponding to a IIIF Range with the "top" viewing hint. Has member Ranges that represent the logical structure, such as chapters within a book, scenes in a film, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TopRange

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A work or intellectual entity, such as a book, film, dissertation, etc. Works have member FileSets representing their physical structure (e.g., pages in a book), and related TopRanges representing their logical structure or structures (e.g., sections and chapters in a book).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Work

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A written composition in prose, usually nonfiction, on a specific topic, forming an independent part of a book or other publication, as a newspaper or magazine.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Article

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A written or printed work of fiction or nonfiction, usually on sheets of paper fastened or bound together within covers.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Book

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A chapter of a book.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Chapter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The status of the publication of a document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Document Status

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A document that presents visual or diagrammatic information.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Image

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A document describing an account or statement describing in detail an event, situation, or the like, usually as the result of observation, inquiry, etc..
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Report

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A document created to summarize research findings associated with the completion of an academic degree.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Thesis

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The academic degree of a Thesis
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Thesis degree

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A thesis reporting the research undertaken during a period of graduate study leading to a doctoral degree.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: doctoral thesis

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A thesis reporting a research project undertaken as part of a graduate course of education leading to a master's degree.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: master's thesis

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: a collection of content items, practice items, and assessment items that are combined based on a single learning objective
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Learning Object

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: a resource that cannot be neatly defined within the scope of any other type (i.e. "other")
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Research Material

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A paper presented at a conference; optionally collected into a Proceedings or a special Journal issue
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Conference Paper

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The digital file (or physical equivalent), if available after the conference, vs. the act of attending/presenting: use ConferencePresentation for information about date/time/location/name of the event where the poster was presented
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Conference Poster

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000112: US Patent Data; US Job Data
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A named collection of data, usually containing only one type of data
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Dataset

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An article reviewing one or more other information resources (a book, one or more other articles, movies, etc)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Review

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:title: Portland Common Data Model
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Ontology for the Portland Common Data Model, intended to underlie a wide array of repository and DAMS applications.

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:title: Portland Common Data Model: Works Extension
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Ontology for a PCDM extension that adds subclasses of pcdm:Object to refine the relationships between a work and its constituent parts. Also establishes links to the IIIF Presentation API.
Accepted for publication after peer reviewing.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: accepted

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Links from a File to its containing Object.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is file of

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Links to a File contained by this Object.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has file

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Links to a subsidiary Object or Collection. Typically used to link to component parts, such as a book linking to a page. Note on transitivity: hasMember is not defined as transitive, but applications may treat it as transitive as local needs dictate.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has member

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Links to a related Object that is not a component part, such as an object representing a donor agreement or policies that govern the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has related object

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Links from an Object or Collection to a containing Object or Collection.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is member of

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Links from an Object to a Object or Collection that it is related to.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is related object of

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A summary of the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Abstract

rdf:Description.terms:description: The distinction between titles and alternative titles is application-specific.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An alternative name for the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Alternative Title

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date of creation of the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date Created

rdf:Description.terms:description: Examples of resources to which a Date Accepted may be relevant are a thesis (accepted by a university department) or an article (accepted by a journal).
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date of acceptance of the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date Accepted

rdf:Description.terms:description: Examples of resources to which a Date Submitted may be relevant are a thesis (submitted to a university department) or an article (submitted to a journal).
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date of submission of the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date Submitted

rdf:Description.terms:description: Description may include but is not limited to: an abstract, a table of contents, a graphical representation, or a free-text account of the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An account of the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Description

rdf:Description.terms:description: Recommended best practice is to identify the resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An unambiguous reference to the resource within a given context.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Identifier

rdf:Description.terms:description: Changes in version imply substantive changes in content rather than differences in format.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource of which the described resource is a version, edition, or adaptation.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Is Version Of
rdf:Description.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

rdf:Description.terms:description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as RFC 4646 [RFC4646].
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A language of the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Language

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A legal document giving official permission to do something with the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: License

rdf:Description.terms:description: Recommended best practice is to identify the related resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Relation
rdf:Description.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

rdf:Description.terms:description: The described resource may be derived from the related resource in whole or in part. Recommended best practice is to identify the related resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource from which the described resource is derived.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Source
rdf:Description.skos:note: This term is intended to be used with non-literal values as defined in the DCMI Abstract Model (http://dublincore.org/documents/abstract-model/). As of December 2007, the DCMI Usage Board is seeking a way to express this intention with a formal range declaration.

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Spatial characteristics of the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Spatial Coverage

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Temporal characteristics of the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Temporal Coverage

rdf:Description.terms:description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the DCMI Type Vocabulary [DCMITYPE]. To describe the file format, physical medium, or dimensions of the resource, use the Format element.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The nature or genre of the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Type
